The Advanced Encryption Standard (AES) is a block cipher scheme that can be used in different modes. The IETF RFC 4309 describes the use of the AES in Counter with CBC-MAC (CCM) mode with an explicit Initialization Vector (IV) as an IPsec Encapsulating Security Payload (ESP) mechanism to provide confidentiality, data origin authentication, and connectionless integrity .

The AES modes specified in IEEE 802.16m are: AES-CCM mode,iii which provides integrity protection, and AES-CTR mode.
